                  </persName>
            . I am a Thames Police officer. On the 24th of October, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, I took the prisoner in charge at Iron gate-stairs, by the water side, with this lump of loaf sugar in a bundle - I asked where he got it; he said he picked it up, and that he belonged to the brig Manley, laying off the Tower, and that a cask had broken - he told me where the master was to be found.</p>
